					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cryogenchaos" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(251810); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=251810&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182955" alt="CryogenChaos" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=251810)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cryogenchaos" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(251810); return false;" >CryogenChaos</a></span> <span class="odate time_1381099727 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 Oct 2013 22:48</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1865177">
									

<p>The plane is the manifestation of the inner rage of Seymour Fitzgerald, specifically the rage against those around him. The victims of the plane are all the people who have at some point pissed this guy off to the point of wishing them dead (or at least mutilated). Seymour, as it were, has a bit of a short fuse, so a lot of people tend to make him angry. For instance, he's never met the optometrist from Atlanta, Georgia. In fact, Seymour has never even <em>been</em> to Atlanta, Georgia. But ███████ ██████████ was driving to his daughter's house in Birmingham, Alabama when he happened to accidentally cut off another driver when he merged into the left lane on the interstate.</p>
<p>Seymour doesn't like bad drivers, you know, especially ones who cut him off.</p>
<p>The anomalous events within the plane are various things that have happened to Seymour during his life. For example, on January 1st, 2001, Seymour was taken to the hospital after his appendix burst. The poor fellow had an extraordinarily high fever, causing him to drift in and out of delirium. In fact, at one point, he could have sworn he was on the cockpit of a plane, but a swift and brutal bout of vomiting snapped him out of it.</p>
<p>Back to the meat of the issue, though, Seymour is a very judgmental person. Whenever he gets mad at someone, he always some variation of the same thing: &quot;One day that asshole will know what it means to be sorry!&quot;</p>
<p>&#8212;</p>
<p>Yeah that kind of sucked.</p>
<p>Anyway, love the rewrite. Everything that made the original intriguing has been upped at least fivefold, and I for one am a fan. +1.</p>

